[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Perpignan banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["translate"],["fr"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Perpignan"]}," (",{"type":"'''","value":["Perpinyà"]}," in catalan) is the capital of the department of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Pyrénées-Orientales"]]},", the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Northern Catalonia"]]}," part of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["France"]]}," and is situated about 15km from the sea. Perpignan is home to about 100 000 people, and has two rivers flowing through it; with the ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/T%C3%AAt_(river) Têt"]}," to the north, and the Basse through the centre.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Autoroute A9, from north (France) and south (Spain)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" D 914 (ex RN114)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Andorra"]]},", N116."]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Dublin"]]}]}," use Aer Lingus (www.aerlingus.com)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Regular line from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Paris"]]}," (Paris - Orly Sud): 5 planes\/ day. (Air France)"]},{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Manchester"]]}]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["England"]]},", use ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.bmibaby.com BMIbaby"]}]}," for cheap flights"]},{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["London"]]}]}," Stansted airport - daily flights, use Ryanair (www.ryanair.com) for cheap flights"]},{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"'''","value":["Charleroi\/Brussels"]}," (3 flights a week), use Ryanair (www.ryanair.com) for cheap flights"]},{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"'''","value":["Birmingham"]}," (3 flights a week) with Ryanair"]},{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"'''","value":["Southampton"]}," (2 flights a week), use Flybe (www.flybe.com) for cheap flights"]},{"type":"*","value":[" From ",{"type":"'''","value":["Bristol"]}," (2 flights a week) - about €44- use Ryanair (www.ryanair.com) "]},"\n- ",{"type":"'''","value":["Shuttle Airport\/Perpignan downtown (€4,50) : 04 68 52 60 70"]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" From all over Europe to ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Girona"]]}]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Spain"]]}," with ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.ryanair.com Ryanair"]}]}]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Perpignan is served by the TGV and the IdTGV. Perpignan-Paris: 5h. soon: Perpignan-Barcelona: 1h."]},"\nFrom ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Girona"]]}]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Spain"]]},", use ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.frogbus.com FROGBUS.com"]}]}," for express bus service from Girona airport to Perpignan\nFrom ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[[","value":[["Girona"]]}]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Spain"]]},", use ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.renfe.es Renfe"]}]}," for trains to Cerbere.\nFrom Cerbere to Perpignan use ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.voyages-sncf.com sncf"]}]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Eurolines : 04 68 34 11 46 - 10, avenue du Général de Gaulle (close to the railway station); www.eurolines.fr"]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\nThe main way to get around in Perpignan (due to its relatively small size) is by foot, but there are buses run by ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.ctpmperpignan.com\/ Compagnie Transports"]}," that go right through the city centre, and then further out, even going as far as ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cabestany"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Canet"]]},". Driving is also a good way to get about, with lots of underground parking in the city centre, but beware, during the summer and 'tourist season' there will be a lot of traffic, and few parking places left.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" The cathedral of St Jean was begun in 1324 and finished in 1509."]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" The 13th century castle of the kings of Majorca sits on the high citadel, surrounded by ramparts, reinforced for Louis XI and Charles V, which were updated in the 17th century by Louis XIV's military engineer Vauban."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\nMusée de l'aviation - created in 1976 by Mr Noettinger, this museum located at \"Mas Palégry\" gathers planes, models and hundreds of original pieces. Open from Monday afternoon to Saturday from April 1st to October 31st.\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Spectator sports:"]}," Perpignan is one of France's rugby hotbeds, and boasts professional teams in both rugby codes:\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["USAP Perpignan"]}," — Plays rugby union (15 a side) in France's Top 14 competition, where it is frequently one of the strongest teams. Home ground is Stade Aimé Giral."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":["Dragons Catalans"]}," — Plays rugby league (13 a side) in Super League, where it is joined by 12 teams from England and one from Wales. Home ground is Stade Gilbert Brutus."]},"\nThe festival Sant Joan is not to be missed. \n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\nThe centre of Perpignan is filled with lots of small boutiques, but there are also large stores such as the department store \"Galeries Lafayette\", and the small shopping centre \"fnac\".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Budget"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Premiere Classe Perpignan"],["url=http:\/\/www.premiere-classe-perpignan.fr\/"],["email="],["address=Chemin Du Mas Palegry Rn9"],["lat="],["long="],["